==English==
===Etymology===
Hindi '''[[मसाला]]''' (masālā) "spice(s)", from Persian '''{{FAchar|[[مصالح]]}}''' (maṣāliḥ) "affairs, materials, spices", plural of '''{{FAchar|[[مصلحت]]}}''' (maṣlaḥat) "affair, policy, best thing to do", both from Arabic, derived from '''{{ARchar|[[صلح]]}}''' (ṣálaḥa) "be fit, competent, usable".  

===Noun===
'''masala'''

# a paste used in Indian cuisine

